com.percussion.design.objectstore
Interface IPSReplacementValue

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable
All Known Implementing Classes:
PSLiteralSet, com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSNamedReplacementValue, PSRelationshipProperty
public interface IPSReplacementValue
extends Cloneable

The IPSReplacementValue interface must be implemented by any class which can be used as a replacement value for conditionals or exit parameters at run-time.

Since:
1.0
Version:

clone

Object clone()
Creates a new instance of this object, deep copying all member variables. If an implementing class has mutable member variables, it must override this method and clone() each of those variables. This method will create a shallow copy if it is not overridden.

Returns:
a deep-copy clone of this instance, never null.
